Service Details: - Support program and classes for expectant parents who are isolated, without support or who are low income- Includes four group classes and one hospital tour- Offers a light snack with classes which is free of charge
Eligibility: - Expectant parents under 19 years of age- Also accepts expectant parents ages 20-25 years with one of the following criteria: single, Isolated (culturally, geographically, socially), low education, low income, experiencing challenges with coping or decision making
How to Apply: Please call to speak with a nurse
